==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''explicare'', "to unfold" or "to explain"

===Verb===
{{en-verb|explicat|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To [[explain]] [[meticulous|meticulously]] or in great [[detail]]; to [[elucidate]]; to [[analyze]].
#:''My homework is to '''explicate''' a poem.''
# to develop a principle, theory, etc.

